---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy | ComplyEaze Tools">
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <h1>Browser-local by design.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Tool files are processed in your browser and are not uploaded by the
        tool. The site may still receive ordinary request metadata while serving
        static pages and assets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="detail-grid" aria-label="Privacy commitments">
    <article>
      <h2>What stays local</h2>
      <p>
        Pasted rows, review text, generated drafts, and downloaded text files are
        handled by code running in your browser. The V0 tools do not create
        accounts, upload files, call an application API, or send tool input to
        ComplyEaze.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>What servers may see</h2>
      <p>
        Static hosting, ingress, certificate, and security systems may process
        ordinary web request metadata such as IP address, user agent, request
        path, timestamp, and TLS details while serving pages and assets.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>What not to paste</h2>
      <p>
        Do not paste real credentials, OTPs, CAPTCHA answers, Aadhaar numbers,
        bank details, portal cookies, full notices, ledgers, or taxpayer
        documents into public issues, screenshots, fixtures, or support threads.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>Professional review</h2>
      <p>
        Outputs are drafts for review. Verify source documents, dates, amounts,
        identities, and statutory positions before sending anything to a client,
        counterparty, portal, authority, or auditor.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
